        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 7 at 4:38PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 438 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Moriarty, moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Moriarty, Estancia and McIntosh.

This includes Interstate 40 between Mile Markers 195 and 209.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
